               <msContents>
                  <msItem class="declaration">
                     <p>
                        <seg type="docType">Declaration of Dame Margaret Brocas &amp; George Baynard concerning the
                        manor of Roch Court in Hampshire.</seg>
                        <placeName key="place_116047">Roche Court (Hampshire)</placeName>. <origDate when="1633">9 Chas. 1. Jul. 1, 1633</origDate>. Indenture made between (1) George Baynard of Basingstoke, Hampshire,
                        gent., and (2) Dame Margaret Brocas widdow, late wife of Sir Pexall Brocas
                        of Little Brickhill, Buckinghamshire, deceased, being a covenant by (1) to
                        (2) concerning the manor of North Farham alias Roch Court, Hampshire and
                        messuages and lands in North Farham, Wickham and Tichfeild, reciting an
                        indenture of 19 Feb 8 Chas. I made between Thomas Brocas of Beaurepaire,
                        Hampshire, son of Dame Margaret, and Dame Margaret and George Baynard, to
                        which corrections are made (signed by Margaret Brocas and George
                        Baynard).</p>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
